'''Sakaguchi Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|12=draft|12=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== [[File:Site of Asahi-sinmeisha, Sakaguchi-Oji.JPG|thumb|Site of Asahi Shinmeisha, Sakaguchi Ōji]] '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' ('''さかぐちおうじ''') was the second {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft|12=draft}} shrine along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft|12=draft}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. Its presumed site is around {{ill|Minami-Oe Park|ja|南大江公園|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Kanzaki-chō|ja|神崎町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chūō-ku, Osaka|ja|中央区 (大阪市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|12=draft|12=draft}}.
There used to be a shrine called {{ill|Asahi Shinmeigū|ja|朝日神明宮|12=draft|12=draft}} in this area, which has since been relocated to {{ill|Konohana-ku, Osaka|ja|此花区|12=draft|12=draft}}. Currently, a small shrine dedicated to {{ill|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin|ja|狸坂大明神|12=draft|12=draft}} stands within Minami-Oe Park. Nearby is the {{ill|Enoki Daimyōjin|ja|榎木大明神|12=draft|12=draft}}, considered a remnant of the Ōji site. Enoki Daimyōjin is a small shrine enshrining a sacred tree, believed to be an {{ill|enoki|ja|エノキ|12=draft|12=draft}} (Chinese hackberry), and is located just south of Minami-Oe Park. Some also consider it an ancient {{ill|Ichirizuka|ja|一里塚|12=draft|12=draft}} (milestone mound).
However, botanical analysis has revealed that the sacred tree is actually an {{ill|enju|ja|槐|12=draft|12=draft}} (Japanese pagoda tree).
[[File:TanukizakaDaimyojin.JPG|thumb|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin]]
== Nearest Stations == * '''Minami-Oe Park and Enoki Daimyōjin:''' {{ill|Osaka Metro Nagahori Tsurumi-ryokuchi Line|ja|Osaka Metro長堀鶴見緑地線|12=draft|12=draft}} – {{ill|Matsuyamachi Station|ja|松屋町駅|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Tanimachi Rokuchome Station|ja|谷町六丁目駅|12=draft|12=draft}} * '''Asahi Shinmeigū:''' {{ill|JR West|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|12=draft|12=draft}} – {{ill|Sakurajima Line (JR Yumesaki Line)|ja|桜島線|JRゆめ咲線|12=draft|12=draft}} – {{ill|Ajikawaguchi Station|ja|安治川口駅|12=draft|12=draft}} == See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Faith|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft|12=draft}} – {{ill|Kiiji Route|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft|12=draft}} : {{ill|Kubotsu Ōji|ja|窪津王子|12=draft|12=draft}} – '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' – {{ill|Kōto Ōji|ja|郡戸王子|en|12=draft|12=draft}} {{Shinto Sidebar}}
