'''Sakaguchi Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== [[File:Site of Asahi-sinmeisha, Sakaguchi-Oji.JPG|thumb|Site of Asahi Shinmeisha, Sakaguchi Ōji]] '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' ('''さかぐちおうじ''') was the second {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} shrine along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodo|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodō|qq=}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. Its presumed site is around {{ill|Minami-Oe Park|ja|南大江公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minami-Oe Park|qq=}} in {{ill|Kanzaki-chō|ja|神崎町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanzaki-chō|qq=}}, {{ill|Chūō-ku, Osaka|ja|中央区 (大阪市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chūō-ku, Osaka|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka City|qq=}}.
There used to be a shrine called {{ill|Asahi Shinmeigū|ja|朝日神明宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asahi Shinmeigū|qq=}} in this area, which has since been relocated to {{ill|Konohana-ku, Osaka|ja|此花区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konohana-ku, Osaka|qq=}}. Currently, a small shrine dedicated to {{ill|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin|ja|狸坂大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanukizaka Daimyōjin|qq=}} stands within Minami-Oe Park. Nearby is the {{ill|Enoki Daimyōjin|ja|榎木大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enoki Daimyōjin|qq=}}, considered a remnant of the Ōji site. Enoki Daimyōjin is a small shrine enshrining a sacred tree, believed to be an {{ill|enoki|ja|エノキ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/enoki|qq=}} (Chinese hackberry), and is located just south of Minami-Oe Park. Some also consider it an ancient {{ill|Ichirizuka|ja|一里塚|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichirizuka|qq=}} (milestone mound).
However, botanical analysis has revealed that the sacred tree is actually an {{ill|enju|ja|槐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/enju|qq=}} (Japanese pagoda tree).
[[File:TanukizakaDaimyojin.JPG|thumb|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin]]
