{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11425069]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:02, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|fr|Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== [[File:Site of Asahi-sinmeisha, Sakaguchi-Oji.JPG|thumb|Site of Asahi Shinmeisha, Sakaguchi Ōji]] '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' ('''さかぐちおうじ''') was the second {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=}} shrine along the [[:en:Kumano Kodō|Kumano Kodō]] pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. Its presumed site is around {{ill|Minami-Oe Park|ja|南大江公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minami-Oe Park|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Kōzaki|Kanzaki-chō]], [[:en:Chūō-ku, Osaka|Chūō-ku, Osaka]], [[:en:Osaka|Osaka City]].
There used to be a shrine called {{ill|Asahi Shinmeigū|ja|朝日神明宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asahi Shinmeigū|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in this area, which has since been relocated to [[:en:Konohana-ku, Osaka|Konohana-ku, Osaka]]. Currently, a small shrine dedicated to {{ill|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin|ja|狸坂大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanukizaka Daimyōjin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} stands within Minami-Oe Park. Nearby is the {{ill|Enoki Daimyōjin|ja|榎木大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enoki Daimyōjin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, considered a remnant of the Ōji site. Enoki Daimyōjin is a small shrine enshrining a sacred tree, believed to be an [[:en:Celtis sinensis|enoki]] (Chinese hackberry), and is located just south of Minami-Oe Park. Some also consider it an ancient [[:en:Ichirizuka|Ichirizuka]] (milestone mound).
However, botanical analysis has revealed that the sacred tree is actually an {{ill|enju|ja|槐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/enju|qq=}} (Japanese pagoda tree).
[[File:TanukizakaDaimyojin.JPG|thumb|Tanukizaka Daimyōjin]]
== Nearest Stations == * '''Minami-Oe Park and Enoki Daimyōjin:''' [[:en:Nagahori Tsurumi-ryokuchi Line|Osaka Metro Nagahori Tsurumi-ryokuchi Line]] – [[:en:Matsuyamachi Station|Matsuyamachi Station]] or [[:en:Tanimachi Rokuchōme Station|Tanimachi Rokuchome Station]] * '''Asahi Shinmeigū:''' [[:en:West Japan Railway Company|JR West]] – [[:en:Sakurajima Line|Sakurajima Line (JR Yumesaki Line)]] – [[:en:Ajikawaguchi Station|Ajikawaguchi Station]] == See Also == * {{ill|Kumano Faith|ja|熊野信仰|1=Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano Three Shrines|lt=Kumano faith|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Faith|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Three Shrines|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 熊野三山}} * [[:en:Kumano Kodō|Kumano Kodō]] – {{ill|Kiiji Route|ja|紀伊路|1=Kiiji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiiji Route|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiiji|qq=}} * {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=}} : {{ill|Kubotsu Ōji|ja|窪津王子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kubotsu Ōji|qq=}} – '''Sakaguchi Ōji''' – {{ill|Kōto Ōji|ja|郡戸王子|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōto Ōji|qq=}} {{Shinto Sidebar}}
